00:06:02.424 --> 00:06:08.305
I'd better talk a little bit about the environment of Japan first.

00:06:08.972 --> 00:06:13.560
The land of Japan is surrounded by the sea

00:06:13.602 --> 00:06:17.272
and 70% of the land is mountainous.

00:06:17.439 --> 00:06:21.110
And a lot of rivers, lakes and small islands.

00:06:21.402 --> 00:06:23.821
Thanks to the four seasons,

00:06:23.862 --> 00:06:27.908
from spring, summer, autumn to winter,

00:06:27.908 --> 00:06:32.746
we receive a lot of blessings such as fish from the sea,

00:06:33.747 --> 00:06:37.584
or vegetables from the mountains, fields and so forth.

00:06:38.419 --> 00:06:42.172
That is why we show our gratitude to nature.

00:06:42.339 --> 00:06:48.011
On the other hand, Japan is also famous for natural disasters

00:06:48.053 --> 00:06:52.057
like typhoons, tsunami or earthquakes.

00:06:57.438 --> 00:07:07.281
We pray not to have these severe natural phenomena while showing gratitude to nature.

00:07:07.656 --> 00:07:18.625
Our ancestors may have thought natural disasters were raised because they disturbed the harmony of nature by their living ways.

00:07:18.876 --> 00:07:26.258
Therefore, they tried to keep the harmony of nature by finding themselves as a part of nature.

00:07:27.259 --> 00:07:34.433
Shinto has been formed based on these two minds: grateful and awesome feeling towards nature.

00:07:35.309 --> 00:07:40.689
We join our hands like this to the sun or to the sea, or to the rivers.

00:07:41.023 --> 00:07:45.277
Those objects are called "kami" in shinto.

00:07:45.277 --> 00:07:49.281
Kami of the sun, kami of the sea, or kami of the mountains.

00:07:49.698 --> 00:07:59.124
Monotheistic religions have only one omnipotent God, but shinto has thousands of God, or "kami".

00:08:00.083 --> 00:08:08.342
So there are one or several enshrined kami at each shrine, but none of them seem to be idolized.

00:08:09.176 --> 00:08:16.183
Instead people are greeting various kami, or kami in general, when they visit the shinto shrine.

00:08:16.183 --> 00:08:26.276
So in this sense, it's not that strange even though the visitors do not know what is enshrined at Meiji Jingu.

00:08:27.277 --> 00:08:34.993
So if you think of religion as a means by which we can find salvation through following God's commandments,

00:08:34.993 --> 00:08:39.164
living righteously and repenting,

00:08:39.331 --> 00:08:44.711
it will be difficult to understand the nature of the shinto faith.

00:08:46.380 --> 00:08:49.883
Shinto has no founder.

00:08:52.177 --> 00:08:57.474
Shinto has no founder, holy scriptures or concept of conversion.

00:08:57.474 --> 00:09:03.897
So there is no single accepted definition of shinto.

00:09:05.023 --> 00:09:09.903
But let me try to explain my view of shinto from two aspects.

00:09:10.737 --> 00:09:15.784
That is connections with God and connections with societies.

00:09:18.453 --> 00:09:27.254
As far as I understand, Monotheistic religions attaches importance to connections with God.

00:09:27.629 --> 00:09:32.301
Because an omnipotent God created this world and mankind

00:09:32.467 --> 00:09:40.601
and mankind can live under God's protection and can attain peace after death.

00:09:41.602 --> 00:09:46.398
To stay connected with God, we need to follow God's will strictly.

00:09:46.940 --> 00:09:49.401
Because of this strictness

00:09:49.776 --> 00:09:52.613
deep faith in God is developed,

00:09:52.988 --> 00:09:56.700
human ethics or religious body are upheld,

00:09:57.034 --> 00:10:00.329
and happiness and peace are maintained, I think.

00:10:01.580 --> 00:10:07.294
So there is another aspect of religion that is connections with societies.

00:10:08.211 --> 00:10:10.964
When we see someone facing difficulties

00:10:11.131 --> 00:10:18.847
we try to help them to overcome their hardships through a variety of methods and actions.

00:10:19.973 --> 00:10:28.106
I am grateful for the help from the world when the big earthquake and tsunami happened 5 years ago.

00:10:29.024 --> 00:10:32.402
Whether it is love, charity or mercy,

00:10:33.070 --> 00:10:42.621
religious values provide people with a clear path towards sharing happiness with each other in the context of social relationships.

00:10:43.705 --> 00:10:51.505
If connections with God place more emphasis on individual pursuit of peace after death,

00:10:51.838 --> 00:11:02.265
then connections with societies orient people towards achieving happiness not only for themselves but also for the many people in this life.

00:11:05.811 --> 00:11:13.110
As I mentioned before, our ancestors thought that we are surrounded by many kami,

00:11:14.486 --> 00:11:16.947
even kami of our ancestors.

00:11:17.364 --> 00:11:20.409
This world is filled with kami.

00:11:20.784 --> 00:11:28.083
You might notice that the concept of kami is quite different from the concept of God.

00:11:30.335 --> 00:11:37.259
In shinto, connection with kami and connections with society are integrated.

00:11:38.427 --> 00:11:45.350
Shinto believes that people receive blessings from countless kami surrounding them.

00:11:45.642 --> 00:11:54.526
And in the course of their lives, they receive energy for their own development or societal growth.

00:11:57.362 --> 00:12:04.035
In Japanese there is an expression, "Ikasarete-iru". Do you understand the meaning of this?

00:12:04.244 --> 00:12:06.079
Ikasarete-iru.

00:12:06.204 --> 00:12:15.130
It's quite hard to translate into English, so I'm not sure if I can explain this accurately.

00:12:15.422 --> 00:12:18.633
But let's take an example:

00:12:19.009 --> 00:12:24.639
Instead of saying, "I live by eating rice",

00:12:25.265 --> 00:12:30.645
we would say, "I'm allowed to live by the rice,"

00:12:30.937 --> 00:12:38.236
which assumes the idea that rice is a blessing that we must be thankful for

00:12:38.403 --> 00:12:42.991
as the efforts of many people went into its cultivation.

00:12:43.074 --> 00:12:49.748
Based on the magnificient working of the sun, rain, soil and microorganisms,

00:12:49.873 --> 00:12:57.506
and furthermore, it was harvested and transported, and placed on store shelves.

00:12:58.965 --> 00:13:04.763
"Itadakimasu", the phrase before eating with joining our hands together,

00:13:04.888 --> 00:13:10.393
has all meanings of our thankfulness.

00:13:12.187 --> 00:13:19.152
So individuals are "ikasarete-iru" through various interactions in society.

00:13:19.903 --> 00:13:27.786
It means that individuals also have an effect on these interactions.

00:13:27.911 --> 00:13:32.707
In my opinion, the reason that Japanese people cherish harmony

00:13:32.749 --> 00:13:41.174
is because they recognize this interconnectedness, consciously or unconsciously.

00:13:41.299 --> 00:13:46.972
In principal, an individual's happiness equals peoples' happiness.

00:13:47.597 --> 00:13:57.315
Many people are mindful to behave in a way that maintains progress of harmony in the context of this interconnectedness.

00:13:57.691 --> 00:14:02.279
I perceive this as shinto's sense of religious value.

00:14:03.154 --> 00:14:11.413
I found an interesting expression in the book "Angels and Demons" by Dan Brown. Have you read this book before?

00:14:11.997 --> 00:14:17.002
No? But you've watched the film of "Angels and Demons"?

00:14:17.377 --> 00:14:21.006
Is that this old?

00:14:21.840 --> 00:14:22.924
No?

00:14:23.300 --> 00:14:25.635
No? Everybody?

00:14:25.844 --> 00:14:27.053
Nobody?

00:14:27.220 --> 00:14:30.348
Yeah, "Angels and Demons".

00:14:32.976 --> 00:14:37.772
OK, anyway, in that book there is an interesting phrase:

00:14:37.772 --> 00:14:43.778
"The planet is an organism. All of us are cells with different purposes."

00:14:43.987 --> 00:14:49.868
"And yet we are intertwined. Serving each other. Serving the whole."

00:14:50.118 --> 00:14:53.079
Don you think this is an interesting expression?

00:14:54.873 --> 00:15:01.546
So in addition, there is a concept called "Jo-Mei-Sei-Choku"

00:15:01.963 --> 00:15:06.301
Meaning "pure, bright, honest and sincere."

00:15:06.426 --> 00:15:09.429
Which is also an important value in shinto.

00:15:10.096 --> 00:15:13.683
So by maintaining purity and sincere heart

00:15:13.683 --> 00:15:19.064
a peaceful and happy social environment will be achieved.

00:15:20.440 --> 00:15:26.947
Purity means dislike of "kegare", or "uncleanliness."

00:15:27.906 --> 00:15:34.329
Kegare links to the term meaning the dying up of one's life force.

00:15:36.039 --> 00:15:41.044
In this state, we cannot unleash our potential energy.

00:15:42.921 --> 00:15:49.719
So please look at this as the potential energy that a new born baby has like the sun.

00:15:50.303 --> 00:15:55.767
However day by day, impurities approach it,

00:15:56.059 --> 00:16:00.563
resulting in weakening its original vitality.

00:16:01.523 --> 00:16:08.071
So in order to get rid of these impurities, shinto has purification in many ways.

00:16:09.322 --> 00:16:13.034
For example in bathing water like this.

00:16:13.868 --> 00:16:15.412
Or like this.

00:16:15.537 --> 00:16:18.039
This is a picture of Meiji Jingu.

00:16:18.206 --> 00:16:24.004
We have this "misogi" or "bathing water" in the cold days of January.

00:16:25.005 --> 00:16:30.677
And you wash your hands and rise your mouth before entering the shrine.

00:16:32.053 --> 00:16:39.227
And at the end of June and December we have big purification ceremonies like this.

00:16:39.602 --> 00:16:45.692
The shinto priest using a wand to cast away the impurities or uncleanliness.

00:16:47.152 --> 00:16:49.029
So by doing so

00:16:50.947 --> 00:16:57.162
we regain the original energy and vitality to live.

00:16:57.871 --> 00:17:04.044
The Japanese peoples' love of bathing is also one example I think.

00:17:05.336 --> 00:17:10.884
Here again I quote a phrase from "Angels and Demons" by Dan Brown:

00:17:11.259 --> 00:17:18.141
"God, Buddha, The Force, Yahweh, the singularity, the unicity point"

00:17:18.308 --> 00:17:22.562
"Call it whatever you like, the result is the same."

00:17:23.271 --> 00:17:31.196
"Science and religion support the same truth - pure energy is the father or creation."

00:17:31.613 --> 00:17:34.199
I think this is also interesting.

00:17:36.493 --> 00:17:39.537
So restore an individual's vivid state

00:17:39.829 --> 00:17:46.586
the support from society, as well as the efforts of the individuals become important.

00:17:48.588 --> 00:17:54.761
The shinto rituals, or "matsuri", may play roles to enforce this vitality.

00:17:56.262 --> 00:17:59.140
Have you joined any matsuri before?

00:18:00.141 --> 00:18:06.272
Some of them, right? People are very crazy for joining matsuri like this.

00:18:06.648 --> 00:18:09.067
Or this one too.

