00:18:13.530 --> 00:18:21.162
And these ladies. This is Awa Odori at Shikoku islands in Tokushima prefecture.

00:18:21.579 --> 00:18:27.544
And even the children are involved in these matsuri.

00:18:28.419 --> 00:18:31.506
They look very vivid I think.

00:18:32.882 --> 00:18:35.927
So beside these big ritual ceremonies

00:18:36.177 --> 00:18:42.392
small rituals or customs can be seen in our life cycle events.

00:18:42.684 --> 00:18:47.856
Like bringing a new born baby to a shinto shrine.

00:18:48.314 --> 00:18:53.444
Or seven, five, three year old children like this.

00:18:54.320 --> 00:18:57.115
And coming of age day.

00:18:57.699 --> 00:19:05.623
So these are important opportunities for us to clean up ourselves, or to show our gratitude for the growth,

00:19:05.790 --> 00:19:11.004
and to feel we are living in the community of this world.

00:19:12.422 --> 00:19:21.890
Personal happiness, society's happiness, is to evolve the existing harmony into a more progressive harmony.

00:19:22.682 --> 00:19:33.902
If I can say, our mission in this life will leave behind a even more harmonious world for future generations,

00:19:35.445 --> 00:19:40.992
while inheriting the harmonious world our ancestors have created.

00:19:42.076 --> 00:19:49.250
Many Japanese people live by sensing the horizontal connections with societies

00:19:49.667 --> 00:19:58.009
coupled with vertical connections with life, connections with past and future.

00:19:59.093 --> 00:20:06.059
Here is a question however: Is this only limited to shinto or Japanese?

00:20:06.976 --> 00:20:12.857
What I have mentioned is just the idea of consideration for other people.

00:20:13.524 --> 00:20:20.323
I believe this is a universal value that cuts across all religions, or all over the world.

00:20:21.783 --> 00:20:25.703
